ianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=329.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  How have light blues affected your solo camps?</span><hr size=1> Since a patch or three ago, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Verant</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> introduced <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  light blue</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> con mobs, which yield some experience.  In essence, it seems that these are mobs that were previously green, but yielded experience, so that the main difference is that we can identify them.  It also appears that <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  blue</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> con was extended to cover some lower levels as well <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  (i.e. some of what might have been light blue are actually blue now)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
My question is, how has this effected your soloing?<br>
<br>
Of course, I prefer partnering or grouping, but some weeks I work late and leave early in the morning, so I only have a couple of hours to play before bed.  So I like to park at a static camp and solo, and if someone joins me, all the better.<br>
<br>
What I have found is that several static outdoor camps I had previously abandoned are now <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  light blue</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, with the occasional <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  blue</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and these are proving worthwhile.  There is one camp with four <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  light blue</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> spawns, with occasional green and blue, on a three minute timer.  Easy to break, and then that is one spawn every 45 seconds.  With a max or near max pet, using <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Arch Mage</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> right clicks for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Lava Shield</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Burnout 3</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, I am able to do sustained kills for the entire time I am there, keep my mana bar fairly full, and get half a blue bubble of experience at 57th level in two casual hours.  There are also nearby similar spawns, so if some lower levels join me, I do even better.<br>
<br>
Yes, I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  do</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> realize that in a real group, in a real dungeon, with steady pulls, I can do better than a quarter blue an hour.  On the other hand, under the circumstances, I do not have time to get a group, get a spot, and get going before beddy bye time.  For late nights/early morning work weeks like these, this seems at least adequate.<br>
<br>
Also, when <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Luclin</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> goes live, this may well be an adequate way to level skills.<br>
<br>
So how do <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  light blues</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> effect <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>your</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> camps?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Summoner of the 57th Bottle of Beer on the Wall<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Ancient Fellowship, Xev</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
